cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.LG. 

This paper deals with data cleaning and estimation of errors in datasets, which is a common problem in many areas of computer science. The focus on crowdsourcing and the need for robust estimators suggests that cs.DB (databases) and cs.AI (artificial intelligence) are likely categories. The use of human workers also suggests cs.HC (human-computer interaction) as a possible category. The need to extrapolate from small gold-standard datasets suggests cs.IR (information retrieval) as a possible category. Finally, the use of statistical techniques for estimation suggests cs.LG (machine learning) as a possible category.
